<TITLE> Cabinet advises moving on oil-gas deals </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 16 (bdnews24.com) The cabinet committee on government purchase has advised the energy and mineral resources ministry to move on appointing companies for exploration of oil and gas in the Bay of Bengal, adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said Tuesday. It also suggested the law ministry be consulted on any legal complexities arising over the Dhaka-Chittagong highway expansion project, he told reporters after a meeting of the purchase committee. He said allocation of Tk 6.41 crore was approved for land development to build a prison in Keraninganj. Approval for a Tk 17.99 crore project to renovate 125 upazila health complexes also came at the meeting. The committee decided to import one lakh metric tonnes of fertiliser from Belarus through the Bangladesh Agriculture Development Corporation, keeping an option to import an extra 50,000 tonnes, if needed. Law adviser AF Hassan Ariff, local government adviser Anwarul Iqbal, agriculture adviser CS Karim, the chief adviser's special assistant M Tamim and cabinet secretary Ali Imam Majumder attended the meeting along with relevant secretaries and officials. bdnews24.
